properties.name: Watch & Act
properties.webBody:
This Watch and Act message is being issued for Flowerdale, Strath Creek, Break O'Day.

Firefighters are taking advantage of the current weather conditions to undertake back burning activities on the southeast side of the fire. As a result, there will be increased smoke. Smoke may be visible in your community for the next few days.

  • The grassfire at Spring Valley Rd, Flowerdale  has spread to nearby bushland and forest, where it has been burning for several days and is not yet under control.
  • There is a threat that it may spread further to nearby grass land. 
  • The risk of spread is on the south-eastern side of the fire. 
  • You need to monitor conditions and be ready to act.
  • Firefighting aircraft and heavy machinery are also in attendance supporting firefighters on the ground. 
Staying close to a building where you can shelter is the safest option, as conditions can change suddenly.

Continue to stay informed and monitor conditions.
What you should do:
  • Monitor changes, including increased wind speed, change in wind direction, smoke or poor visibility that indicates the situation is changing. 
  • People with pre-existing lung or heart conditions should rest as much as possible and keep away from the smoke. minimise smoke exposure by reducing your level of exercise during smoky conditions. If practical, stay indoors and keep windows closed until the smoke passes. People experiencing symptoms due to smoke exposure should seek medical advice or call NURSE-ON-CALL on 1300 60 60 24
If the situation changes you will need to leave quickly. Plan to:
  • Take your pets, medications, mobile phone and charger.
  • Travel to the home of family or friends that are away from the warning area.
  • Emergency services may not be able to help you if you decide to stay.
Impacts in your area:
  • The following road is closed: Sping Valley Rd between the Whittlsea-Yea Rd and Upper King Parrot Creek rd.
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.

The next update is expected by 23/02/2023 05:00 pm or as the situation changes.
Spring Valley Rd Fire map
Use multiple sources to stay informed:
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires)
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.
Accessibility:
The following services can help you, or someone you know, access information during an emergency.
  • To access this information in other languages, call the Translating and Interpreting Service on 131 450 (freecall) and ask them to call VicEmergency Hotline.
  • If you are deaf, hard of hearing, or have a speech/communication impairment contact National Relay Service on 1800 555 677 and ask them to call the VicEmergency Hotline.

Firefighters are taking advantage of the current weather conditions to undertake back burning activities on the southeast side of the Flowerdale-Spring Valley Rd fire, in the vicinity of Minto Rd and Barina Heights. Due to the increased northerly wind speeds, this will result in smoke being visible in your community for the next few days. 


There is no immediate threat to the community and no action is required.
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.

The next update is expected by 26/02/2023 11:50 am or as the situation changes.

properties.name: Advice
properties.webBody:
This Advice message is being issued for Ballyrogan, Buangor, Challicum.

This message replaces the advice issued today at 12:45 PM. 

  • There is a grassfire at Hillside Rd, Buangor that is not yet under control.
  • This grassfire is travelling in a southerly direction towards Geelong Road. 
There is currently no threat to you, but you should stay informed and monitor conditions.
What you should do: 
  • Keep the roads clear so emergency services can respond. 
  • If you do not have a plan, decide what you will do if the situation changes. Find information on protecting yourself and your family: https://www.cfa.vic.gov.au/plan-prepare/am-i-at-risk/grassfires-rural.
Impacts in your area: 
  • Firefighters and aircraft are attending to this fire. 
  • Smoke may be visible from nearby communities and roads. 
This message was issued by Country Fire Authority.

The next update is expected by 23/02/2023 03:40 pm or as the situation changes.

Use multiple sources to stay informed: 
  • www.emergency.vic.gov.au
  • VicEmergency Hotline - freecall 1800 226 226
  • VicEmergency app
  • Facebook or Twitter (#vicfires)
  • Tune in to ABC Local Radio, commercial and designated community radio stations, or Sky News TV.
Accessibility:
